    Brill's New Pauly: "Myrinus, Elegant epigrammatic poet in the ‘Garland’ of Philippus. Four poems are extant, 
    showing him as a skillful imitator of Leonidas [3] of Tarentum
    however, he also displayed an independent creativity,..." from Albiani, Maria Grazia (Bologna). "Myrinus."
    Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online. 
    Tufts University Library. 07 December 2009
  </mads:note>
  <mads:note>Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1867, p. 1129: "Myrinus,
